{{CommentUpdateEvent}} does not implement {{ConfluenceEntityUpdated}}, which means that code can't treat {{CommentUpdateEvent}} instances and {{PageUpdateEvent}} instances both as {{ConfluenceEntityUpdated}}.

{quote}The 'Favourite Pages' section is populated by the labels plugin. All profiles, including anonymous users share the global label set, including any labels named 'Favourite'. This is then reflected on the global dashboard page, which cannot be edited by anonymous users. When an anonymous user clicks on the 'star' to remove a page from the favourites list, they receive an error.

A user who has logged in, will by default use the global 'Favourite' labels. Once the user has modified the list, by adding or removing a favourite page, their personal dashboard will be updated to use a personal list.

I believe this function is "working" as intended, but the result for anonymous users may not be the expected result.{quote}

